Theorem 43.Theorem:
Let $a_{i} \in(0, \infty), i=1,2, \ldots, n$, and $\alpha_{i} \in[0,1], i=1,2, \ldots, n$, be such that $\alpha_{1}+\alpha_{2}+\cdots+\alpha_{n}=1$.
Then
$$
\begin{equation*}
a_{1}^{\alpha_{1}} a_{2}^{\alpha_{2}} \cdots a_{n}^{\alpha_{n}} \leq a_{1} \alpha_{1}+a_{2} \alpha_{2}+\cdots+a_{n} \alpha_{n} \tag{7.9}
\end{equation*}
$$

Theorem 40.Theorem:
Let $f:(a, b) \rightarrow \mathbb{R}$ be a convex function on the interval $(a, b)$. Let $n \in \mathbb{N}$ and $\alpha_{1}, \alpha_{2}, \ldots, \alpha_{n} \in(0,1)$ be real numbers such that $\alpha_{1}+\alpha_{2}+\cdots+\alpha_{n}=1$. Then for any $x_{1}, x_{2}, \ldots, x_{n} \in(a, b)$ we have
$$
f\left(\sum_{i=1}^{n} \alpha_{i} x_{i}\right) \leq \sum_{i=1}^{n} \alpha_{i} f\left(x_{i}\right)
$$
i.e.
$$
\begin{equation*}
f\left(\alpha_{1} x_{1}+\alpha_{2} x_{2}+\cdots+\alpha_{n} x_{n}\right) \leq \alpha_{1} f\left(x_{1}\right)+\alpha_{2} f\left(x_{2}\right)+\cdots+\alpha_{n} f\left(x_{n}\right) \tag{7.2}
\end{equation*}
$$
